Amy Johnson faces two assault charges after she allegedly grabbed a McDonald's worker by the neck and scratched her face . 
  The 38-year-old said she became aggressive because the fries had spilled out of their containers and the worker used her bare hands to repack them . 
  Ms Johnson was a passenger in a BMW when she went through the drive-through at Stanmore in Sydney's inner west . 
  She allegedly grabbed the teenager by the face and grabbed her $60 order of fries . 
  She is facing serious assault charges and appeared in court on Thursday . 
 